    {
      "name": "TOLIB",
      "description": "To library",
      "help": "To library (TOLIB)\n\nSpecifies the library in which the duplicate object is to be created.\n\nNote: If the library is in an auxiliary storage pool (ASP), the object to be duplicated must be a valid object type that can reside in an ASP. If this object type is not a valid type that can reside in an ASP, an error message is sent.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *FROMLIB, *SAME, *CURLIB",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*FROMLIB",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "positional": 4,
      "placeholder": "*FROMLIB",
      "basic": true,
      "valueMap": {
        "*FROMLIB": "*SAME"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "NEWOBJ",
      "description": "New object",
      "help": "New object (NEWOBJ)\n\nSpecifies name of the new object. A name must be specified here if *SAME or *FROMLIB is specified for the To library (TOLIB) parameter and the same auxiliary storage pool device is specified for both the From ASP device (ASPDEV) parameter and the To ASP device (TOASPDEV) parameter. The names of members in a database file to be duplicated remain the same in the new file.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *OBJ, *SAME",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*OBJ",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "positional": 5,
      "placeholder": "*OBJ",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "ASPDEV",
      "description": "From ASP device",
      "help": "From ASP device (ASPDEV)\n\nSpecifies the auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name where storage is allocated for the library containing the object to be duplicated (the From library (FROMLIB) parameter). If the library is in an ASP that is not part of the thread's library name space, this parameter must be specified to ensure the correct object is duplicated. If this parameter is used when *LIBL or *CURLIB is specified for the FROMLIB parameter, * is the only valid value.\n\nNote: To specify a specific auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name, you must have use (*USE) authority for each ASP device in the ASP group.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *, *CURASPGRP, *SYSBAS",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "placeholder": "*",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "TOASPDEV",
      "description": "To ASP device",
      "help": "To ASP device (TOASPDEV)\n\nSpecifies the auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name where storage is allocated for the library to contain the new object (the To library (TOLIB) parameter). If the library is in an ASP that is not part of the thread's library name space, this parameter must be specified to ensure the object is duplicated into the correct library. If this parameter is used when *CURLIB is specified for the TOLIB parameter, either TOASPDEV(*) must be specified or TOASPDEV(*ASPDEV) must be specified and the From ASP device (ASPDEV) parameter must be *.\n\nNote: To specify a specific auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name, you must have use (*USE) authority for each ASP device in the ASP group.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *ASPDEV, *, *CURASPGRP, *SYSBAS",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*ASPDEV",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "placeholder": "*ASPDEV",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "DATA",
      "description": "Duplicate data",
      "help": "Duplicate data (DATA)\n\nSpecifies whether the data records in database physical files or save files are copied to the new object. Members of database physical files are copied whether or not the data contained in them is copied.\n\nNOTES:",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*NO",
      "attributes": {
        "restricted": true,
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*NO",
          "value": "*NO"
        },
        {
          "label": "*YES",
          "value": "*YES"
        }
      ],
      "promptControl": [
        {
          "controlParameter": "OBJTYPE",
          "countRelation": "EQ",
          "count": 1,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "FILE"
            },
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "*ALL"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "CST",
      "description": "Duplicate constraints",
      "help": "Duplicate constraints (CST)\n\nSpecifies whether any constraints associated with existing database physical files are copied to the newly-created files. The specified value is not used for objects which are not database physical files.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*YES",
      "attributes": {
        "restricted": true,
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*YES",
          "value": "*YES"
        },
        {
          "label": "*NO",
          "value": "*NO"
        }
      ],
      "promptControl": [
        {
          "controlParameter": "OBJTYPE",
          "countRelation": "EQ",
          "count": 1,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "FILE"
            },
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "*ALL"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "TRG",
      "description": "Duplicate triggers",
      "help": "Duplicate triggers (TRG)\n\nSpecifies whether any triggers associated with existing database files are copied to the newly-created files. The specified value is not used for objects which are not database files.\n\nNote: There are special considerations of which to be aware relating to the duplication of triggers. For example, the duplication will differ depending on whether or not the trigger program associated with the existing file was in the same library as the existing file. For additional information, see the Database category in the IBM i Information Center at http://www.ibm.com/systems/i/infocenter/.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*YES",
      "attributes": {
        "restricted": true,
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*YES",
          "value": "*YES"
        },
        {
          "label": "*NO",
          "value": "*NO"
        }
      ],
      "promptControl": [
        {
          "controlParameter": "OBJTYPE",
          "countRelation": "EQ",
          "count": 1,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "FILE"
            },
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "*ALL"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "FILEID",
      "description": "Duplicate file identifiers",
      "help": "Duplicate file identifiers (FILEID)\n\nSpecifies whether the file level and member level identifiers of the existing database file will be used for the newly-created file. The specified value is not used for objects which are not database files.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*NO",
      "attributes": {
        "restricted": true,
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*NO",
          "value": "*NO"
        },
        {
          "label": "*YES",
          "value": "*YES"
        }
      ],
      "promptControl": [
        {
          "controlParameter": "OBJTYPE",
          "countRelation": "EQ",
          "count": 1,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "FILE"
            },
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "*ALL"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "ACCCTL",
      "description": "Duplicate access control",
      "help": "Duplicate access control (ACCCTL)\n\nSpecifies whether any row access controls, or column access controls associated with existing database physical files are copied to the newly-created files. The specified value is not used for objects which are not database physical files.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*ALL",
      "attributes": {
        "restricted": true,
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*ALL",
          "value": "*ALL"
        },
        {
          "label": "*ROW",
          "value": "*ROW"
        },
        {
          "label": "*COL",
          "value": "*COL"
        },
        {
          "label": "*NONE",
          "value": "*NONE"
        }
      ],
      "promptControl": [
        {
          "controlParameter": "OBJTYPE",
          "countRelation": "EQ",
          "count": 1,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "FILE"
            },
            {
              "relation": "EQ",
              "compareValue": "*ALL"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "examples": [
    {
      "code": "CRTDUPOBJ OBJ(FILEA) FROMLIB(LIB1) OBJTYPE(*FILE) TOLIB(LIB2) DATA(*YES)"
    },
    {
      "code": "CRTDUPOBJ OBJ(FILEB) FROMLIB(LIB3) OBJTYPE(*FILE) NEWOBJ(FILEDUP) DATA(*NO) CST(*NO) TRG(*NO) FILEID(*YES)"
    }
  ],
  "source": {
